WEBVTT

00:52.487 --> 00:55.011
This story ends
before you were born.

01:12.202 --> 01:13.595
Mother.

01:19.166 --> 01:20.515
Again.

01:23.866 --> 01:25.302
When we woke up

01:25.302 --> 01:28.000
feeling hands that
were no longer there,

01:28.000 --> 01:30.699
the elders told us
that it was the work of ghosts

01:31.395 --> 01:32.570
or Satan.

01:36.444 --> 01:40.012
Or that we were lying
to get attention.

01:40.012 --> 01:43.451
Or that it was an act
of wild female imagination.

01:49.283 --> 01:50.719
It went on for years.

01:53.461 --> 01:54.636
To all of us.

02:04.211 --> 02:06.169
It felt like weightlessness.

02:07.823 --> 02:10.217
It felt like drifting over
what used to be real.

02:13.394 --> 02:16.397
- It felt like a banishment,

02:16.397 --> 02:18.094
as though we had
no invitation anymore

02:18.094 --> 02:19.922
to be a part of the real.

02:29.584 --> 02:31.107
I used to wonder
who I would be

02:31.107 --> 02:33.979
if it hadn't happened to me.

02:33.979 --> 02:36.460
I used to miss the person
I might have been.

02:37.592 --> 02:39.115
I don't anymore.

02:41.813 --> 02:43.467
Because it's doomsday

02:43.467 --> 02:44.947
and a call to prayer.

02:46.209 --> 02:47.341
It's both.

02:54.478 --> 02:55.827
We caught one of them.

02:56.437 --> 02:57.873
I saw his face.

02:59.091 --> 03:00.745
And then he named the others.

03:02.007 --> 03:03.226
Come on.

03:12.279 --> 03:13.541
Eventually the attackers

03:13.541 --> 03:15.804
were taken to the police
in the city

03:15.804 --> 03:17.197
for their own protection.

03:24.900 --> 03:26.554
Almost all of the men
of the colony

03:26.554 --> 03:27.816
went to the city to post bail

03:27.816 --> 03:29.165
for the attackers.

03:30.079 --> 03:31.602
We were given two days

03:31.602 --> 03:33.822
to forgive the attackers
before they returned.

03:36.303 --> 03:37.782
If we did not forgive them

03:37.782 --> 03:39.958
we would be ordered
to leave the colony

03:39.958 --> 03:42.918
and be denied entry
into the Kingdom of Heaven.

03:54.277 --> 03:55.452
Do nothing.

03:58.325 --> 03:59.413
Stay and fight.

04:02.851 --> 04:03.852
Leave.

04:32.184 --> 04:35.623
Girls in our colony
had very little schooling.

04:35.623 --> 04:38.016
We hardly knew
how to read or to write.

04:38.887 --> 04:40.541
But that day,

04:40.541 --> 04:42.020
we learned how to vote.

05:36.423 --> 05:37.815
The vote was tied between

05:37.815 --> 05:40.862
staying and fighting,
or leaving.

05:40.862 --> 05:43.778
So three families
including yours and mine

05:43.778 --> 05:45.170
were elected to decide

05:45.170 --> 05:46.911
what the women
of the colony would do.

05:56.660 --> 05:59.794
Your mother had asked,
August, the school teacher,

05:59.794 --> 06:02.231
to take the minutes
of our meeting.

06:02.231 --> 06:06.148
August came back to the colony
just recently.

06:06.148 --> 06:09.107
His family had been
excommunicated years ago.

06:17.638 --> 06:20.510
August had loved your mother
since he was a boy.

06:38.006 --> 06:39.529
Before we began,

06:39.529 --> 06:41.183
your grandmother, Agata,

06:41.183 --> 06:43.533
told us we had to honor
our service to each other.

06:44.665 --> 06:47.189
We had to represent it.

06:47.189 --> 06:48.886
Just as the disciples
were washed

06:48.886 --> 06:51.541
by Jesus at the Last Supper,

06:51.541 --> 06:54.109
knowing that his hour
had come.

06:57.721 --> 06:59.462
We only had 24 hours

06:59.462 --> 07:02.334
to imagine what world
you would be born into.

07:06.121 --> 07:08.340
It is a part
of our faith to forgive.

07:08.340 --> 07:10.255
We have always forgiven those
who have wronged us.

07:10.255 --> 07:11.343
Why not now?

07:11.343 --> 07:12.823
Because now we know better.

07:12.823 --> 07:14.434
We will be excommunicated,

07:14.434 --> 07:16.131
forced to leave the colony
in disgrace

07:16.131 --> 07:17.785
if we do not forgive
these men.

07:18.786 --> 07:20.222
And if we are excommunicated,

07:20.222 --> 07:23.181
we forfeit our place
in Heaven.

07:23.181 --> 07:26.446
How could any of you
live with the fear of that?

07:26.446 --> 07:28.622
These are
legitimate fears.

07:29.971 --> 07:31.494
How can we address them?

07:31.494 --> 07:34.018
The only
important thing to establish

07:34.018 --> 07:35.933
is if we forgive the men.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.415
So that we will be allowed
to enter the gates of Heaven.

07:40.808 --> 07:42.200
You can laugh
all you like, Salome,

07:42.200 --> 07:43.550
but we will be forced
to leave the colony

07:43.550 --> 07:44.594
if we don't forgive the men.

07:45.813 --> 07:47.162
How will the Lord
when he arrives

07:47.162 --> 07:48.903
find the women
if we aren't in the colony?

07:48.903 --> 07:50.513
Jesus is able
to return to life,

07:50.513 --> 07:51.906
live for thousands of years

07:51.906 --> 07:53.385
and then drop down
to earth from Heaven

07:53.385 --> 07:54.604
to scoop up his supporters,

07:54.604 --> 07:56.301
surely he'd also
be able to locate

07:56.301 --> 07:57.433
a few women
who left their colony.

07:57.433 --> 07:58.521
Let's stay on track.

07:58.521 --> 07:59.740
All right. I'll stay on track.

07:59.740 --> 08:01.655
I cannot forgive them.

08:01.655 --> 08:03.352
I will never forgive them.

08:04.571 --> 08:05.876
I can't either.

08:07.617 --> 08:08.792
But we want to enter

08:08.792 --> 08:10.098
the Kingdom of Heaven
when we die.

08:14.668 --> 08:16.365
We have everything
we want here.

08:16.365 --> 08:17.540
No.

08:17.540 --> 08:18.846
Want less.

08:21.065 --> 08:22.371
Does entering
the Kingdom of Heaven

08:22.371 --> 08:24.025
mean nothing to any of you?

08:24.025 --> 08:25.592
Surely there must be something

08:25.592 --> 08:28.159
worth living for in this life,
not only in the next.

08:40.432 --> 08:42.043
Autje!

08:42.043 --> 08:43.305
- See you soon. It's all right.
-  Sorry.

08:43.305 --> 08:44.872
It's all right.
It will be all right.

08:54.229 --> 08:56.361
Your grandmother
used to say,

08:56.361 --> 08:58.450
"Find out where
you can be of help

08:58.450 --> 09:00.757
"and leave what
you can't help behind."

09:01.889 --> 09:03.020
I think that's easier

09:03.020 --> 09:04.761
when you're old like her.

09:04.761 --> 09:06.850
So we must decide now

09:06.850 --> 09:09.940
to stay and fight, or leave.

09:09.940 --> 09:12.160
Those are the options
in front of us.

09:13.640 --> 09:15.816
We will not do nothing.

09:19.341 --> 09:22.431
I want to talk about
my horses Ruth and Cheryl.

09:26.043 --> 09:27.828
When Ruth and Cheryl
are frightened by Dueck's dogs

09:27.828 --> 09:30.700
on the mile road
that leads to the church,

09:30.700 --> 09:32.615
their initial instinct
is to bolt.

09:33.834 --> 09:34.922
Whoa!

09:36.663 --> 09:38.665
These horses
don't organize meetings

09:38.665 --> 09:40.623
to decide what they will do.

09:41.102 --> 09:42.233
They run.

09:42.233 --> 09:44.584
But, Greta,
we are not animals.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.890
We have been preyed upon
like animals.

09:46.890 --> 09:49.371
Maybe we should respond
like animals.

09:49.371 --> 09:50.459
In my lifetime,
I have seen

09:50.459 --> 09:52.417
horses confront angry dogs

09:52.417 --> 09:54.463
and try to stomp them
to death.

09:54.463 --> 09:55.899
Animals don't always flee.

09:55.899 --> 09:57.597
Is this how we want
to teach our daughters

09:57.597 --> 09:59.250
to defend themselves?

09:59.250 --> 10:00.425
By fleeing?

10:00.425 --> 10:01.601
Not fleeing but leaving.

10:01.601 --> 10:02.819
I was just talking
about leaving.

10:02.819 --> 10:03.951
I would rather
stand my ground

10:03.951 --> 10:05.126
and shoot each man
in the heart

10:05.126 --> 10:06.562
and bury 'em in a pit
than flee.

10:06.562 --> 10:08.216
And I'll deal with God's wrath
if I have to.

10:08.216 --> 10:10.000
Salome, Aunt Greta is talking
about leaving not fleeing.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.872
The word "fleeing"
wasn't what she meant.

10:11.872 --> 10:14.918
Yeah. Please forgive my mother
for using the wrong word.

10:14.918 --> 10:16.137
It's a sin so outrageous

10:16.137 --> 10:17.747
that Salome has taken it
upon herself

10:17.747 --> 10:19.967
to rectify for the sake
of all humanity.

10:19.967 --> 10:22.491
"Leaving" and "fleeing"
are different words

10:22.491 --> 10:24.580
with different meanings.

10:24.580 --> 10:26.669
They each say
something about us.

10:32.196 --> 10:33.894
August,

10:33.894 --> 10:36.070
what do you make
of all of this?

10:36.070 --> 10:37.898
Do you have an opinion too?

10:39.551 --> 10:40.596
I think...

10:42.424 --> 10:44.687
I think that it is possible

10:44.687 --> 10:46.776
to leave something
or someone...

10:49.561 --> 10:51.955
in one frame of mind

10:51.955 --> 10:55.437
and arrive elsewhere
in another

10:55.437 --> 10:58.048
entirely unexpected
frame of mind.

10:58.048 --> 10:59.833
I want to stay and fight.

10:59.833 --> 11:01.095
But won't we lose the fight
to the men

11:01.095 --> 11:03.097
and be forced
to forgive them anyway?

11:03.097 --> 11:04.446
I want to stay and fight too.

11:04.446 --> 11:05.969
No one's surprised
that you do.

11:05.969 --> 11:07.536
All you do is fight.

11:07.536 --> 11:09.320
Is this really
how we are to decide

11:09.320 --> 11:11.671
the fates of all the women
in this colony?

11:11.671 --> 11:13.150
Just another vote

11:13.150 --> 11:15.239
where we put an X
next to our position?

11:15.239 --> 11:17.067
I thought we were here
to do more than that.

11:17.067 --> 11:18.329
You mean talk more about

11:18.329 --> 11:19.374
forgiving the men
and doing nothing.

11:19.374 --> 11:20.767
Everything else is insane.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.551
But none of you
will listen to reason.

11:22.551 --> 11:24.248
Well, why are you
here with us?

11:24.248 --> 11:25.685
Why are you still here with us
if that is what you believe?

11:25.685 --> 11:27.121
Just leave with the rest
of the do nothing women.

11:27.121 --> 11:30.080
She is my daughter
and I want her here with us.

11:32.039 --> 11:33.649
Is forgiveness
that's forced upon us

11:33.649 --> 11:34.737
true forgiveness?

11:36.957 --> 11:39.176
Keep nonsense
like that to yourself please.

11:39.742 --> 11:40.917
Autje, get down!

11:40.917 --> 11:42.919
Autje,
listen to your mother!

11:43.615 --> 11:44.791
Behave yourself.

11:44.791 --> 11:46.575
Don't you hear
the rafter's creaking?

11:46.575 --> 11:48.446
Do you want
the roof to cave in?

11:52.450 --> 11:54.191
Many of us
saw ourselves from above.

11:56.150 --> 11:57.847
I'm not sure if it was God

11:57.847 --> 12:00.545
and we were seeing ourselves
through his eyes.

12:02.373 --> 12:04.375
Or if we
just couldn't be there.

12:07.074 --> 12:08.815
In our own bodies.

12:12.775 --> 12:13.950
How'd you
get up there?

12:13.950 --> 12:15.386
It was a miracle.

12:15.386 --> 12:17.737
A miracle from God.

12:17.737 --> 12:19.347
-  Of course.
-  What else?

12:20.348 --> 12:22.393
Where I come from,

12:22.393 --> 12:24.134
where your mother comes from,

12:25.309 --> 12:28.443
we didn't talk
about our bodies.

12:28.443 --> 12:29.966
So when something
like this happened

12:29.966 --> 12:32.534
there was no language for it.

12:32.534 --> 12:36.277
And without language for it,
there was a gaping silence.

12:38.061 --> 12:41.108
And in that gaping silence
was the real horror.

13:46.782 --> 13:48.262
Neitje's mother hanged herself

13:48.262 --> 13:50.960
after the attacks
had gone on for a while.

13:53.180 --> 13:55.051
It made us wonder,

13:55.051 --> 13:56.879
why did our feet
keep moving forward

13:56.879 --> 13:58.446
when hers just couldn't.

13:59.577 --> 14:00.883
What sets us apart

14:00.883 --> 14:02.711
from the ones
who get left behind?

14:07.455 --> 14:09.283
This is never going to end.

14:09.283 --> 14:11.067
We'll be dead
and they'll still be talking.

14:11.067 --> 14:12.547
Or worse.
We'll have to live through it.

14:15.071 --> 14:16.464
August, I think
you should make lists

14:16.464 --> 14:18.683
of the pros and cons
of both options.

14:18.683 --> 14:21.077
"Staying and fighting"
and "leaving."

14:24.559 --> 14:26.082
Post it on the wall.

14:29.607 --> 14:30.913
Make sure and write large.

14:30.913 --> 14:32.045
Why?

14:32.045 --> 14:33.916
We can't read it.

14:33.916 --> 14:35.352
No, but we'll keep it here
as an artifact

14:35.352 --> 14:37.093
for others to discover.

14:39.269 --> 14:40.792
I think the first heading
should say,

14:40.792 --> 14:43.230
"staying and fighting"
and under that write "pros".

14:43.230 --> 14:45.232
Who will go first?

14:45.232 --> 14:47.364
We're starting with
staying and fighting, pros.

14:47.364 --> 14:49.714
Why do we need this?
This is our home.

14:51.194 --> 14:52.326
That's what you believe,

14:52.326 --> 14:54.067
it's not what
everyone believes.

14:54.067 --> 14:55.285
- Excuse me.

14:55.285 --> 14:57.026
Forgive me.
Excuse me, um...

14:57.026 --> 14:59.942
May I request that you
take it in turns speaking

14:59.942 --> 15:02.553
so that I can understand
what each of you is saying.

15:02.553 --> 15:03.772
It takes me
a second to transcribe.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.208
Should we put up our hands

15:05.208 --> 15:06.775
as though we are children
in your schoolhouse?

15:08.037 --> 15:09.212
I...

15:09.212 --> 15:10.953
I apologize.

15:10.953 --> 15:13.129
We won't have to leave.

15:13.129 --> 15:14.783
- Sorry.
- Will you just write it down?

15:15.523 --> 15:16.698
Under pros.

15:16.698 --> 15:18.961
Salome has had
a brilliant idea

15:18.961 --> 15:20.963
that if we stay
we won't have to leave.

15:20.963 --> 15:22.486
We won't
have to figure out

15:22.486 --> 15:24.097
where we are going
or experience the uncertainty

15:24.097 --> 15:26.360
of not knowing
where we are going.

15:26.360 --> 15:27.448
We don't have a map.

15:27.448 --> 15:28.884
That's absurd.

15:28.884 --> 15:30.494
The only certainty we'll know
is uncertainty,

15:30.494 --> 15:32.279
no matter where we are.

15:32.279 --> 15:33.758
Neitje? Autje?

15:33.758 --> 15:35.935
Do you have something
to add to the list?

15:37.632 --> 15:39.634
We won't have
to leave the people we love.

15:39.634 --> 15:41.723
Well, we could bring
our loved ones

15:41.723 --> 15:43.290
with us if we leave.

15:43.290 --> 15:44.944
How?

15:44.944 --> 15:47.598
What does that mean?
That we move the whole colony?

15:47.598 --> 15:49.165
What could that possibly mean?

15:49.165 --> 15:51.559
We could create
the possibility of a new order

15:51.559 --> 15:54.997
right here in a place
that is familiar to us.

15:54.997 --> 15:57.826
Not simply familiar,
but a place that is ours.

15:57.826 --> 15:59.480
Do we need
to write the cons?

15:59.480 --> 16:02.048
Isn't it obvious
that we must stay and fight?

16:02.048 --> 16:04.833
Cons. We won't be forgiven.

16:06.052 --> 16:07.444
May I say something?

16:08.489 --> 16:09.707
Please.

16:09.707 --> 16:11.144
Would it be a good idea
before we list

16:11.144 --> 16:13.015
the pros and cons
of "staying and fighting"

16:13.015 --> 16:14.712
to talk about
exactly what it is

16:14.712 --> 16:15.975
we're fighting for?

16:15.975 --> 16:17.411
It's obvious.

16:17.411 --> 16:18.629
We are fighting for our safety

16:18.629 --> 16:19.935
and for our freedom
from attacks.

16:19.935 --> 16:22.590
But what would
that mean to us?

16:22.590 --> 16:24.374
Perhaps we need a statement
which describes

16:24.374 --> 16:25.767
what we want the colony
to be like

16:25.767 --> 16:27.682
after winning the fight.

16:27.682 --> 16:29.162
Perhaps we need
to understand more

16:29.162 --> 16:30.728
what it is
we are fighting to achieve,

16:30.728 --> 16:33.296
not only what we are fighting
to destroy.

16:34.863 --> 16:36.734
Are we staying
or are we going?

16:39.389 --> 16:40.782
Ona, please tell us more

16:40.782 --> 16:43.002
about the statement
you're thinking about.

16:46.092 --> 16:47.397
Men and women would make

16:47.397 --> 16:50.009
all decisions
for the colony collectively.

16:51.097 --> 16:53.751
Women would be
allowed to think.

16:53.751 --> 16:57.451
Girls will be taught
to read and to write.

16:57.451 --> 16:59.670
The schoolhouse must display
a map of the world

16:59.670 --> 17:03.022
so that we can begin
to understand our place in it.

17:03.022 --> 17:05.198
A new religion,
taken from the old

17:05.198 --> 17:07.026
but focused on love

17:08.462 --> 17:10.942
would be created
by the women of the colony.

17:12.118 --> 17:13.771
Our children would be safe.

17:17.558 --> 17:18.994
"Collectively."

17:22.563 --> 17:24.565
You sound
like August's mother.

17:31.006 --> 17:32.703
Ona, you're a dreamer.

17:33.748 --> 17:36.055
We're women without a voice.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.447
We have nothing to return to.

17:37.447 --> 17:39.406
Even the animals
are safer in their homes

17:39.406 --> 17:41.321
than we women are.

17:41.321 --> 17:43.584
All we have are our dreams.

17:43.584 --> 17:45.499
So of course we are dreamers.

17:46.848 --> 17:48.415
And you want to hear my dream?

17:51.461 --> 17:53.594
I dream that people
who speak nonsense,

17:53.594 --> 17:55.117
who have no grasp on reality,

17:55.117 --> 17:57.337
are not put in charge
of making statements.

17:59.513 --> 18:02.037
What if the men
refuse to meet our demands?

18:03.995 --> 18:05.084
Sorry.

18:09.566 --> 18:10.698
We'll kill them.

18:11.916 --> 18:12.917
No, Ona.

18:23.972 --> 18:25.147
What if the men
who are in prison

18:25.147 --> 18:26.148
are not guilty?

18:29.499 --> 18:30.544
Mother?

18:30.544 --> 18:31.719
Autje.

18:31.719 --> 18:32.850
Why are you asking
if they're...?

18:32.850 --> 18:34.156
Autje, shush.

18:34.156 --> 18:35.331
We caught one of them.

18:36.767 --> 18:38.117
I saw him.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.553
But only one.

18:39.553 --> 18:41.163
Yes, only one,
but he named the others.

18:41.163 --> 18:42.904
But what if he was lying?

18:45.254 --> 18:46.647
We must consider this.

18:46.647 --> 18:49.911
No! That is not
our responsibility

18:49.911 --> 18:51.173
because we aren't in charge

18:51.173 --> 18:53.697
of whether or not
they are punished.

18:53.697 --> 18:55.482
We know that
we've been attacked by men.

18:55.482 --> 18:57.571
Not by ghosts or Satan

18:57.571 --> 18:59.312
as we were led to believe
for so long.

18:59.312 --> 19:02.663
We know that we've not
imagined these attacks.

19:02.663 --> 19:05.666
That we were made unconscious
with cow tranquilizer.

19:05.666 --> 19:09.104
We know that we are bruised,
and infected,

19:09.104 --> 19:12.629
and pregnant, and terrified,
and insane,

19:12.629 --> 19:14.805
and some of us are dead.

19:14.805 --> 19:17.199
We know that
we must protect our children.

19:17.199 --> 19:20.463
Regardless of who is guilty.

19:20.463 --> 19:24.119
All right, Salome. Thank you.
Please, sit down, hmm.

19:25.555 --> 19:26.556
Hmm.

19:48.926 --> 19:50.276
Shall we move on?

19:52.278 --> 19:53.844
It is possible
the men in prison

19:53.844 --> 19:55.324
are not guilty of the attacks,

19:55.324 --> 19:58.022
but are they guilty
of not stopping the attacks?

19:58.022 --> 19:59.241
Are they guilty of knowing

19:59.241 --> 20:00.764
about the attacks
and doing nothing?

20:00.764 --> 20:02.244
How should we know
what they're guilty of or not?

20:02.244 --> 20:03.811
But we do know.

20:03.811 --> 20:06.248
We do know that the conditions
have been created by men

20:06.248 --> 20:08.642
and that these attacks
have been made possible

20:08.642 --> 20:11.384
because of the circumstances
of the colony.

20:11.384 --> 20:12.733
And those circumstances

20:12.733 --> 20:15.257
have been created
and ordained by the men.

20:15.257 --> 20:17.172
But wait,
aren't you suggesting

20:17.172 --> 20:19.870
that the attackers
are as much victims

20:19.870 --> 20:22.482
as the victims of the attacks?

20:22.482 --> 20:24.353
That all of us,
men and women

20:24.353 --> 20:26.181
are victims
of the circumstances

20:26.181 --> 20:28.314
from which the colony
has been created.

20:32.013 --> 20:33.623
In a sense, yes.

20:33.623 --> 20:36.931
So then, even if the court
finds them guilty or innocent,

20:38.193 --> 20:40.326
they are...

20:40.326 --> 20:42.110
after all innocent.

20:44.460 --> 20:46.201
Yes, I would say so.

20:49.248 --> 20:51.250
- The elders called them evil.
-  That's not true.

20:51.250 --> 20:52.555
It's the elder's
quest for power

20:52.555 --> 20:53.861
that is responsible.

20:53.861 --> 20:55.036
Because they needed
to have those...

20:55.036 --> 20:56.646
Those they'd have power over.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.169
And those people are us.

20:58.169 --> 20:59.867
And they have taught
the lesson of power

20:59.867 --> 21:01.695
to the boys and men
of the colony,

21:01.695 --> 21:04.959
and the boys and men
have been excellent students.

21:06.090 --> 21:08.267
Don't we all
want some sort of power?

21:09.093 --> 21:10.269
I think so.

21:11.052 --> 21:12.227
But I'm not sure.

21:13.359 --> 21:14.708
But we caught them.

21:15.361 --> 21:16.666
We caught them.

21:18.189 --> 21:20.757
Yes, you did.

21:20.757 --> 21:23.282
Then why are you
making it so complicated?

21:23.282 --> 21:26.285
This is very, very boring.

21:27.982 --> 21:29.897
We could ask the men to leave.

21:32.378 --> 21:34.293
Ask the men to leave?

21:37.774 --> 21:41.082
None of us have ever
asked the men for anything.

21:41.082 --> 21:42.649
Not a single thing.

21:44.041 --> 21:47.044
Not even for
the salt to be passed.

21:47.044 --> 21:50.613
Not even for a penny,
or a moment alone.

21:50.613 --> 21:54.095
Or to take the washing in,
or to open a curtain,

21:54.095 --> 21:57.272
or to go easy
on the small yearlings.

21:57.272 --> 21:59.927
Or to put your hand
on the small of my back

21:59.927 --> 22:03.191
while I try again
for the 12th or 13th time

22:03.191 --> 22:05.759
to push a baby out of my body.

22:09.502 --> 22:11.242
Isn't it interesting

22:11.242 --> 22:15.377
that the one and only request
we women would have of the men

22:15.377 --> 22:17.292
would be for them to leave?

22:30.914 --> 22:33.830
Asking the men to leave
is not an option.

22:34.265 --> 22:35.310
Oh!

22:37.051 --> 22:39.358
I'd like you to imagine
Ruth and Cheryl.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.620
No. Not again.

22:43.318 --> 22:44.493
Please stop.

22:45.712 --> 22:48.236
Look. August is still
taking the minutes.

22:50.020 --> 22:53.415
I can't believe August
is still taking the minutes.

22:56.287 --> 22:57.811
Sometimes I think
people laugh

22:57.811 --> 22:59.726
as hard as they'd like to cry.

23:02.903 --> 23:05.688
August, you must think
we're all lunatics.

23:06.080 --> 23:08.125
I don't.

23:08.125 --> 23:10.737
And it doesn't matter
what I think, anyway.

23:11.868 --> 23:13.435
Is that true?

23:13.435 --> 23:15.045
Do you really think it doesn't
matter what you think?

23:19.136 --> 23:21.704
How would you feel
if in your entire life

23:21.704 --> 23:23.532
it never mattered
what you thought?

23:25.621 --> 23:27.971
But I'm not here to think.

23:27.971 --> 23:31.018
I'm here to take the minutes
of your meeting.

23:31.018 --> 23:33.281
But if in your entire life
you truly felt

23:33.281 --> 23:35.196
it didn't matter
what you thought,

23:35.196 --> 23:36.893
how would that make you feel?

23:47.295 --> 23:48.644
When we've
liberated ourselves,

23:48.644 --> 23:51.168
we will have to ask ourselves
who we are.

24:35.735 --> 24:37.476
Will we be done
by supper time?

24:37.476 --> 24:40.130
I have to give
little Miep her antibiotics.

24:40.130 --> 24:41.784
Where did you get antibiotics?

24:43.438 --> 24:44.613
She walked.

24:45.658 --> 24:47.137
She walked for
a day and a half

24:47.137 --> 24:49.096
to the mobile clinic

24:49.096 --> 24:51.098
with Miep on her back.

