26:10.307 --> 26:13.615
slow to anger, rich in loving
kindness and forgiveness.

26:20.927 --> 26:23.407
Well, let's take a break.

26:33.940 --> 26:36.507
- Melvin.

26:39.902 --> 26:41.077
You're it.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.483
Not one word
about my smoking.

26:56.223 --> 26:57.703
Honestly, I'm sick of it.

26:57.703 --> 26:59.530
Okay,
I'm coming over here.

27:00.531 --> 27:02.664
Watch out!

27:02.664 --> 27:04.753
Is she always
going to be like this now?

27:06.886 --> 27:07.887
Like what?

27:09.062 --> 27:10.585
A man.

27:10.585 --> 27:12.631
Is Nettie always
going to be a man now?

27:19.159 --> 27:21.291
Later,
we understood that Nettie

27:21.291 --> 27:23.816
didn't become a man
because of what happened.

27:25.774 --> 27:27.950
Nettie had never
felt like a woman.

27:29.648 --> 27:32.259
Now pretending
had become impossible.

27:47.187 --> 27:48.971
Is my brother listening?

27:55.151 --> 27:56.631
Hello, little brother.

28:00.374 --> 28:02.898
I don't know
if the baby was yours,

28:02.898 --> 28:05.684
or if it was
one of your friends.

28:08.382 --> 28:10.993
I think it
was likely yours though...

28:13.430 --> 28:15.476
because there was something
wrong with it.

28:20.873 --> 28:22.352
I loved it.

28:23.614 --> 28:24.877
I think.

28:28.619 --> 28:30.491
Isn't that strange?

28:39.718 --> 28:41.371
I won't speak of it.

28:42.546 --> 28:44.157
Or anything else.

28:46.725 --> 28:47.943
Ever again.

28:55.472 --> 28:56.604
But...

28:56.604 --> 28:57.779
But what?

28:57.779 --> 29:00.042
She doesn't
speak anymore.

29:00.042 --> 29:01.217
You all right?

29:01.217 --> 29:02.610
She speaks
to the children.

29:02.610 --> 29:04.525
Kind of.

29:04.525 --> 29:06.309
I think they call her Melvin.

29:26.329 --> 29:30.725
You know, during
the Second World War in Italy,

29:30.725 --> 29:33.510
civilians would hide
in bomb shelters.

29:34.250 --> 29:35.730
Volunteers were needed

29:35.730 --> 29:38.777
to power the generators
that provided electricity.

29:40.126 --> 29:41.736
They rode bikes.

29:44.130 --> 29:47.089
And when you were swinging
from the rafter earlier,

29:47.089 --> 29:50.614
I was, uh, reminded of this.

29:50.614 --> 29:52.616
You would have been
the perfect volunteer.

29:54.836 --> 29:56.490
If we were in a bomb shelter.

29:58.709 --> 30:01.190
Where would I ride the bike to
in such a small space?

30:01.190 --> 30:04.324
Oh, well, uh,
the bike would be stationary.

30:09.808 --> 30:11.505
I have to get the water
to the horses.

30:18.512 --> 30:19.774
Watch this.

30:27.303 --> 30:28.827
Oh!

30:32.091 --> 30:33.788
I'll bet you didn't learn
how to do things like that

30:33.788 --> 30:35.834
when you went to university.

30:35.834 --> 30:37.879
Only facts about
stationary bicycles

30:37.879 --> 30:39.359
in far off places.

30:41.927 --> 30:43.798
I suppose I shouldn't be
too sad then.

30:44.494 --> 30:45.931
That I won't ever go.

30:51.284 --> 30:53.895
Why were you forced
to leave the colony?

30:53.895 --> 30:55.854
My mother questioned things.

30:56.898 --> 30:58.291
She questioned God?

30:58.944 --> 31:00.336
Not God.

31:00.336 --> 31:01.381
Power.

31:02.469 --> 31:05.733
The rules made
in the name of God.

31:05.733 --> 31:09.432
And she encouraged others
to question things too.

31:09.432 --> 31:10.912
Like Ona?

31:10.912 --> 31:11.913
Yes.

31:13.132 --> 31:14.916
Ona knew her well.

31:16.309 --> 31:17.745
Did she die?

31:29.888 --> 31:31.193
But sometimes,

31:31.193 --> 31:32.716
listening to you all
speaking today

31:32.716 --> 31:35.284
I can hear her so clearly.

31:38.113 --> 31:40.594
Why did the elders
let you come back?

31:40.594 --> 31:42.596
Well, I went to university

31:42.596 --> 31:46.121
so I could serve a purpose
and teach the boys.

31:47.079 --> 31:48.384
Too late.

32:02.137 --> 32:04.009
I want to help.

32:05.445 --> 32:06.925
And I don't know how.

32:08.491 --> 32:10.493
You came back for Ona,
didn't you?

32:11.755 --> 32:13.496
The way you look at her is

32:14.758 --> 32:15.759
funny.

32:17.196 --> 32:19.372
I don't know why
she won't just marry you.

32:19.372 --> 32:21.591
You both say so much
that doesn't make sense.

32:41.698 --> 32:43.352
Mama.

32:46.051 --> 32:47.661
All residents, please come out

32:47.661 --> 32:49.010
of your homes to be counted
for the 2010 census.

32:49.010 --> 32:51.186
Hey, hey, hey.
Shoo, shoo, shoo!

32:51.186 --> 32:52.796
Away. Away!

32:55.974 --> 32:57.714
Please come out
and be counted now.

32:57.714 --> 32:59.064
Please come out of your homes

32:59.064 --> 33:01.109
to be counted
for the 2010 census.

33:15.167 --> 33:17.430
All residents must come out
of their homes

33:17.430 --> 33:20.041
to be counted
for the 2010 census.

33:28.484 --> 33:29.529
Whoo!

33:38.364 --> 33:41.019
All right.
You want to try this one?

33:44.500 --> 33:46.067
This is the 2010 census.

33:46.067 --> 33:47.416
Please come out of your homes

33:47.416 --> 33:49.549
to be counted
for the 2010 census.

33:55.468 --> 33:57.209
- Tickle, tickle, tickle.

34:10.526 --> 34:13.486
I'm here to collect data
for the 2010 census.

34:13.486 --> 34:15.096
Please come out
of your homes now

34:15.096 --> 34:16.271
to be counted.

34:20.014 --> 34:21.102
Let's go.

34:21.102 --> 34:22.364
Why?

34:22.364 --> 34:23.800
Let's just... Let's go.

34:40.600 --> 34:42.080
The ladies standing
in front of me.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.125
- How old are you?

34:44.125 --> 34:46.040
- I'm 15.
- I'm 16.

34:46.040 --> 34:48.129
Okay.
So you must have boyfriends.

34:48.129 --> 34:49.522
Oh!

34:49.522 --> 34:50.523
- No. We don't have boyfriends.
- No boyfriend?

34:53.743 --> 34:55.136
I'll see
you ladies again.

34:55.136 --> 34:56.572
- Mm-hmm
-  Take care.

35:07.192 --> 35:12.327
♪ Homecoming queen ♪

35:12.327 --> 35:16.157
