♪ E'er was given ♪

40:34.301 --> 40:35.955
If we do leave the colony,

40:35.955 --> 40:38.436
how will we live with the pain
of never seeing our brothers

40:38.436 --> 40:39.915
and our sons again?

40:41.177 --> 40:42.352
The men?

40:57.542 --> 40:58.499
Time will heal.

41:01.067 --> 41:05.114
Our freedom and safety
are the ultimate goals.

41:05.114 --> 41:08.466
And it is men who prevent us
from achieving those goals.

41:10.990 --> 41:12.470
But not all men.

41:27.920 --> 41:30.488
Perhaps not men,

41:30.488 --> 41:32.359
but a way of seeing the world,
and us women,

41:32.359 --> 41:33.665
which has been allowed
to take hold

41:33.665 --> 41:35.623
of men's hearts and minds.

41:38.713 --> 41:41.194
So if we leave...
if we leave

41:41.194 --> 41:43.283
I will never see
my brothers again?

41:44.980 --> 41:46.504
Who will
take care of them?

41:47.635 --> 41:48.897
Of them all?

41:50.333 --> 41:52.379
We can't know
if we will stay or leave

41:52.379 --> 41:53.859
before we resolve

41:53.859 --> 41:56.339
these last-minute concerns.

41:57.819 --> 41:59.995
I wouldn't call
the future of our relationship

41:59.995 --> 42:02.737
with the boys and men we love
"last-minute concerns."

42:28.981 --> 42:30.199
There we go.

42:43.909 --> 42:48.609
It was all waiting
to happen before it happened.

42:48.609 --> 42:50.524
You could look back
and follow the breadcrumbs

42:50.524 --> 42:52.831
along the path
that led to violence.

42:53.701 --> 42:55.616
When we looked back,

42:55.616 --> 42:58.358
we could see
that it had been everywhere,

42:58.358 --> 43:00.403
whether it was happening yet
or not.

43:01.361 --> 43:03.581
Hi.

43:16.071 --> 43:17.290
Hi.

43:30.999 --> 43:32.610
I'll get you some water.

43:44.056 --> 43:45.797
There's no cup or anything.

44:16.305 --> 44:18.351
It's good
that you're here, August.

44:20.179 --> 44:22.355
To remind us
of what's possible.

44:24.226 --> 44:25.967
Because it's easy to forget.

44:34.846 --> 44:36.064
I'm so sorry, Ona.

44:39.764 --> 44:40.939
One day I'd like to hear that

44:40.939 --> 44:42.767
from someone
who should be saying it.

44:55.736 --> 44:57.129
Why does love...

44:58.217 --> 45:00.567
The absence of love,
the end of love,

45:00.567 --> 45:02.090
the need for love,

45:03.048 --> 45:05.224
result in so much violence?

45:11.621 --> 45:12.622
Ona.

45:14.799 --> 45:15.756
Ona.

45:18.454 --> 45:20.282
I could take care of you

45:20.848 --> 45:22.154
and your child.

45:25.592 --> 45:26.593
I would like to.

45:30.728 --> 45:31.816
I, um...

45:31.816 --> 45:33.774
I know,

45:33.774 --> 45:35.036
but you don't have
to say the words.

45:38.170 --> 45:40.912
If I were married,
I wouldn't be myself.

45:41.956 --> 45:43.741
So the person you love
would be gone.

45:56.362 --> 45:57.798
Your child...

46:01.410 --> 46:02.629
If we stay
and we don't win the fight,

46:02.629 --> 46:04.413
my child will be given

46:05.371 --> 46:07.112
to another family here.

46:08.722 --> 46:10.898
Maybe even the family
of my attacker.

46:13.335 --> 46:15.250
If we stay
and don't win the fight.

46:19.515 --> 46:21.387
You won't let that happen. No.

46:21.953 --> 46:22.954
No.

46:24.869 --> 46:26.131
No, I won't.

46:47.500 --> 46:49.850
August,
we need to discuss options

46:49.850 --> 46:51.373
for the men
and the older boys,

46:51.373 --> 46:52.853
if the women decide to leave.

46:52.853 --> 46:54.724
Which is a waste of time
because we're not leaving.

46:54.724 --> 46:56.596
The men should leave with us
if they wish.

46:56.596 --> 46:58.337
Then what on earth
is the point of us leaving?

46:58.337 --> 47:00.295
Well, they could be allowed
to join the women later

47:00.295 --> 47:02.167
once the women
have established themselves

47:02.167 --> 47:03.951
and are thriving.

47:03.951 --> 47:05.431
Should we add

47:05.431 --> 47:08.608
"thriving as a collective,
literate community"?

47:08.608 --> 47:10.305
Literate's your word.
Not ours.

47:10.305 --> 47:11.785
We don't need your university
language to make our plans.

47:11.785 --> 47:13.526
Put it in.
We know what it means.

47:13.526 --> 47:14.962
Continue, Greta.

47:14.962 --> 47:17.225
Young boys,
simple-minded boys of any age,

47:17.225 --> 47:19.706
Cornelius who's confined
to a wheelchair,

47:19.706 --> 47:20.881
will accompany the women.

47:20.881 --> 47:22.796
I vote for the first option.

47:22.796 --> 47:24.406
The men should leave with us
if they wish.

47:24.406 --> 47:25.668
The first option is ridiculous

47:25.668 --> 47:27.322
and should be
crossed off the list.

47:27.322 --> 47:28.410
Why are some ideas
written down and considered,

47:28.410 --> 47:30.325
and others crossed out?

47:32.110 --> 47:34.721
I want to leave.
I'd like to strangle myself.

47:34.721 --> 47:35.896
Mariche, it's possible
that all the men

47:35.896 --> 47:37.376
would choose to leave with us.

47:37.376 --> 47:39.378
And then all we'd be doing
is recreating our colony

47:39.378 --> 47:40.814
with all of its
dangers elsewhere.

47:40.814 --> 47:41.946
And the men
would definitely

47:41.946 --> 47:43.295
leave with us because

47:43.295 --> 47:44.687
they can't survive without us.

47:44.687 --> 47:45.950
Well, not for longer
than a day or two.

47:45.950 --> 47:47.168
We have not
decided to leave.

47:47.168 --> 47:48.735
I'd like to remind everyone
of that.

47:48.735 --> 47:50.519
And how can we leave
at all if we've never

47:50.519 --> 47:52.957
been allowed to even see
a map of the world?

47:52.957 --> 47:55.611
I can secure
a world map for you.

47:55.611 --> 47:59.485
I also have a, um,
map of this specific region.

47:59.485 --> 48:01.052
Well, that will do.

48:01.052 --> 48:03.445
It's not like we are planning
to travel the planet.

48:03.445 --> 48:05.012
Perhaps we are.

48:05.012 --> 48:06.361
Did you know
that the migration period

48:06.361 --> 48:08.668
for butterflies
and dragonflies is so long

48:08.668 --> 48:10.191
that it's often
only the grandchildren

48:10.191 --> 48:12.498
that arrive
at the intended destination?

48:14.239 --> 48:15.805
Yes. So, it...

48:17.938 --> 48:19.374
Yes.

48:19.374 --> 48:21.376
Perhaps, if we went beyond
where the map showed us,

48:21.376 --> 48:24.075
we could create
our own map as we go.

48:24.075 --> 48:26.033
So now you want to leave, Ona?

48:31.778 --> 48:33.649
Are you all right,
Mejal?

48:36.957 --> 48:39.351
Nope. She's having
one of her episodes.

48:41.353 --> 48:43.224
Father Almighty,

48:43.224 --> 48:45.966
in all humility
and supplication we ask Thee

48:45.966 --> 48:47.489
for Thy abundant kindness

48:48.055 --> 48:49.404
at this moment.

48:49.404 --> 48:51.537
We beseech Thee

48:51.537 --> 48:54.975
to have mercy
on our sister Mejal.

48:54.975 --> 48:57.412
- Please, in your beneficence,

48:57.412 --> 48:59.197
heal her.

48:59.197 --> 49:01.373
- And please...

49:01.373 --> 49:04.680
...we ask of Thee, envelop her

49:04.680 --> 49:07.509
in your strength
and everlasting love,

49:07.509 --> 49:09.163
and please drive out
the sickness

49:09.163 --> 49:11.035
which afflicts her now.

49:28.530 --> 49:29.967
Help me up.

49:29.967 --> 49:31.925
Praise be to God.

49:36.147 --> 49:37.539
Why is it
only Mejal has these...?

49:37.539 --> 49:38.714
Be quiet.

49:38.714 --> 49:39.889
We were all attacked.

49:40.847 --> 49:41.979
Not all of us need to draw

49:41.979 --> 49:43.676
so much attention
to ourselves.

49:47.419 --> 49:49.029
What attention?

49:49.029 --> 49:50.204
I speak less
than all of you put together.

49:50.204 --> 49:51.379
How have I offended you?

49:51.379 --> 49:53.381
You have
these attacks.

49:53.381 --> 49:55.644
You smoke.

49:55.644 --> 49:59.213
Why? Why is it so much
harder for you than for us?

49:59.213 --> 50:01.346
We were all attacked.
All of us.

50:01.346 --> 50:05.002
We are wasting our time
by passing this burden,

50:05.002 --> 50:07.178
this sack of stones,
from one to the next,

50:07.178 --> 50:10.094
by pushing our pain away.

50:10.094 --> 50:13.401
Let's absorb it ourselves.
Let's inhale it.

50:13.401 --> 50:14.489
Let's digest it.

50:15.273 --> 50:17.797
Let's process it into fuel.

50:23.368 --> 50:24.891
Speak, Mejal.

50:25.631 --> 50:26.936
We are listening.

50:31.028 --> 50:33.160
They made us
disbelieve ourselves.

50:38.600 --> 50:41.473
That was worse than...

50:44.824 --> 50:46.043
Mejal.

50:54.703 --> 50:55.791
Klaas, when he returns,

50:55.791 --> 50:57.402
may take horses or livestock

50:57.402 --> 50:58.664
that we would need
along the way.

50:58.664 --> 51:00.231
Along the way?

51:00.231 --> 51:01.536
We're not leaving.

51:05.018 --> 51:06.976
You are changing
your mind, Ona.

51:06.976 --> 51:09.240
I don't believe
that's a sin, is it?

51:11.155 --> 51:13.853
How will
we be forgiven for all this?

51:13.853 --> 51:15.985
How will we be forgiven,

51:15.985 --> 51:18.727
if not by the elders
whom we have disobeyed?

51:18.727 --> 51:22.035
Perhaps there will be
other elders or men of God

51:22.035 --> 51:23.819
who will be able
to forgive our sins.

51:23.819 --> 51:26.474
We do not need to be forgiven
by the men of God

51:26.474 --> 51:27.823
for protecting our children

51:27.823 --> 51:29.173
from the depraved actions
of vicious men

51:29.173 --> 51:30.435
who are often
the very same men

51:30.435 --> 51:32.350
we're meant to ask
for forgiveness!

51:34.178 --> 51:36.658
If God is a loving God then...

51:36.658 --> 51:38.225
He will forgive us himself.

51:39.574 --> 51:40.793
If God is a vengeful God

51:40.793 --> 51:42.751
then He has created us
in His image.

51:44.623 --> 51:46.842
If God is omnipotent,

51:46.842 --> 51:48.540
then why has He not protected

51:48.540 --> 51:50.803
the women and girls
of this colony?

51:55.982 --> 51:58.245
I will destroy

51:58.245 --> 52:02.075
any living thing
that harms my child.

52:04.991 --> 52:07.298
I will tear it limb from limb.

52:08.168 --> 52:10.170
I will desecrate its body

52:10.170 --> 52:12.172
and I will bury it alive.

52:13.478 --> 52:14.957
I will challenge God
on the spot

52:14.957 --> 52:16.133
to strike me dead

52:16.133 --> 52:17.308
if I have sinned

52:17.308 --> 52:19.745
by protecting my child
from evil,

52:19.745 --> 52:22.835
and by destroying that evil
that it may not harm another!

52:23.792 --> 52:25.533
I will lie,

52:26.708 --> 52:28.797
I will hunt, I will kill.

52:28.797 --> 52:30.495
I will dance on graves

52:30.495 --> 52:33.106
and I will burn
forever in hell

52:33.106 --> 52:35.239
before I allow another man

52:35.239 --> 52:37.066
to satisfy his violent urges

52:37.066 --> 52:39.982
with the body
of my four-year-old child!

53:08.620 --> 53:11.449
I suggest we think
about what is good.

53:13.712 --> 53:15.279
"Whatever is true,

53:16.280 --> 53:18.107
"whatever is honorable,

53:19.108 --> 53:20.719
"whatever is just,

53:21.633 --> 53:23.374
"whatever is pure,

53:23.374 --> 53:25.767
"whatever is pleasing,

53:25.767 --> 53:27.639
"whatever is commendable,

53:28.466 --> 53:30.729
"if there is any excellence

53:30.729 --> 53:34.080
"and if there
is anything worthy of praise,

53:34.080 --> 53:36.865
"think about these things

53:36.865 --> 53:40.173
"and the peace of God
be with you."

53:42.306 --> 53:44.525
I will become a murderer
if I stay.

54:21.345 --> 54:23.434
I know what these are.
These are letters.

54:23.434 --> 54:25.262
But what are these?

54:25.262 --> 54:28.003
They're commas.

54:28.003 --> 54:31.529
They signify a short pause,
or a breath in the text.

54:35.141 --> 54:37.186
There's also a butterfly
called a comma.

54:38.449 --> 54:40.146
- Is that so?
- Mm-hmm.

55:00.166 --> 55:01.341
-  Salome.

55:03.735 --> 55:07.565
If you will become a murderer
by staying here in the colony,

55:07.565 --> 55:09.088
side by side with the men

55:09.088 --> 55:11.351
who are responsible
for the attacks,

55:12.396 --> 55:13.614
then you must,

55:15.573 --> 55:17.357
to protect your own soul,

55:18.053 --> 55:19.751
leave the colony.

55:21.013 --> 55:22.623
We are not all murderers.

55:22.623 --> 55:23.929
Not yet.

55:23.929 --> 55:25.278
I have done
what the verse

55:25.278 --> 55:26.845
from Philippians instructed,

55:26.845 --> 55:29.195
which is to think
about what is good,

55:30.152 --> 55:32.198
what is just, what is pure,

55:32.198 --> 55:33.547
what is excellent.

55:35.114 --> 55:36.463
Pacifism.

55:39.205 --> 55:40.946
Pacifism is good.

55:40.946 --> 55:42.164
Any violence

55:42.904 --> 55:44.515
is unjustifiable.

55:45.429 --> 55:49.694
By staying here, we women

55:49.694 --> 55:52.436
will be betraying
the central tenet of our faith

55:52.436 --> 55:53.828
which is pacifism,

55:56.004 --> 55:57.615
because by staying

55:59.921 --> 56:03.229
we will knowingly
be placing ourselves

56:04.535 --> 56:08.452
in a direct collision course
with violence,

56:10.149 --> 56:13.065
either by us or against us.

56:14.675 --> 56:19.071
This colony is the only home
I've ever known.

56:21.290 --> 56:23.249
And I don't want to leave.

56:23.945 --> 56:25.338
But by staying,

56:26.165 --> 56:27.993
we'll be inviting harm.

56:29.255 --> 56:31.257
We will be in a state of war.

56:31.257 --> 56:35.043
We will turn this colony
into a battlefield.

56:38.699 --> 56:40.962
We cannot
become murderers.

56:40.962 --> 56:43.487
And we cannot endure
any more violence,

56:45.706 --> 56:47.404
which is why we must leave.

57:09.643 --> 57:10.688
I've also been thinking

57:10.688 --> 57:13.647
about the verse
from Philippians

57:13.647 --> 57:15.867
and I've been thinking
about what is good.

57:17.259 --> 57:18.696
Freedom is good.

57:19.740 --> 57:21.786
It is better than slavery.

57:23.048 --> 57:24.789
Forgiveness is good.

57:25.790 --> 57:27.487
It's better than revenge.

57:28.706 --> 57:32.013
And hope for the unknown
is good,

57:32.013 --> 57:34.581
it is better than
hatred of the familiar.

57:34.581 --> 57:36.627
And what about security,

57:37.628 --> 57:40.544
and safety, and home,
and family?

57:41.675 --> 57:44.591
What about marriage,

57:46.724 --> 57:50.118
and love, Ona?

57:50.118 --> 57:52.599
I don't know
about those things,

57:52.599 --> 57:54.035
any of them.

57:55.036 --> 57:56.734
Except for love

57:57.778 --> 58:00.302
and... even love
is mysterious to me.

58:01.216 --> 58:02.566
And I believe that my home

58:02.566 --> 58:04.132
is with my mother,
and my sister,

58:04.132 --> 58:06.657
and my unborn child,
wherever that may be.

58:09.050 --> 58:11.183
Will you not hate that child?

58:14.403 --> 58:15.840
That child's the child
of a man

58:15.840 --> 58:17.581
who inspires
violent thoughts in you.

58:22.673 --> 58:25.240
I already love this child
more than anything.

58:26.590 --> 58:28.592
He or she
is as innocent and lovable

58:28.592 --> 58:30.115
as the evening sun.

58:30.115 --> 58:33.248
So too was the child's father
when he was born.

58:37.514 --> 58:38.776
But, if you're saying

58:38.776 --> 58:41.648
that forgiveness
is better than revenge...

58:43.781 --> 58:46.392
Aren't you saying
that we must stay here

58:46.392 --> 58:47.785
and forgive the men?

58:47.785 --> 58:50.831
We cannot forgive
because we are forced to.

58:53.399 --> 58:58.056
But, with some distance
perhaps I am able

58:59.927 --> 59:03.017
to understand how these crimes
may have occurred.

59:04.410 --> 59:06.238
And with that distance,

59:06.238 --> 59:08.719
maybe I am able
to pity these men,

59:10.459 --> 59:12.331
perhaps forgive them.

59:13.245 --> 59:15.029
And even love them.

59:17.379 --> 59:19.773
Not fighting. But moving.

59:20.687 --> 59:26.432
Always moving. Never fighting.
Just moving.

59:26.432 --> 59:29.957
Never fighting. Just moving.
Never fighting. Always moving.

59:29.957 --> 59:31.611
Would you snap out of it?

59:31.611 --> 59:32.743
You snap out of it.

59:32.743 --> 59:34.092
All of you
snap out of it.

59:34.092 --> 59:36.181
Have you lost your minds?
The sun is gone.

59:39.227 --> 59:42.404
I want to tell another story
about Ruth and Cheryl.

59:51.326 --> 59:52.719
I was always frightened

59:52.719 --> 59:55.548
of the northern road
out of the colony.

59:57.637 --> 1:00:00.205
There are so many gullies
on either side of the road.

1:00:03.991 --> 1:00:07.647
The buggy used to lurch
side to side.

1:00:07.647 --> 1:00:09.388
Ruth and Cheryl were simply

1:00:09.388 --> 1:00:11.433
following my commands
of the reins,

1:00:12.609 --> 1:00:15.263
but, they were
jerky and frenetic.

1:00:15.263 --> 1:00:17.352
And it was dangerous.

1:00:19.616 --> 1:00:22.444
It was only when I learned
to focus my gaze

1:00:22.444 --> 1:00:25.099
far down ahead of me

1:00:25.099 --> 1:00:26.579
and not on the road

1:00:26.579 --> 1:00:28.712
immediately in front
of Ruth and Cheryl,

1:00:28.712 --> 1:00:30.888
that I started to feel safe.

1:00:39.897 --> 1:00:41.986
Leaving will give us

1:00:41.986 --> 1:00:44.858
the more farseeing perspective
we need

1:00:45.642 --> 1:00:47.034
to forgive.

1:00:51.648 --> 1:00:55.434
Which is to love properly

1:00:55.434 --> 1:00:58.785
and keep the peace,
according to our faith.

1:01:00.352 --> 1:01:01.745
Therefore, our leaving

1:01:01.745 --> 1:01:04.486
wouldn't be
an act of cowardice

1:01:04.486 --> 1:01:05.749
or abandonment.

1:01:05.749 --> 1:01:06.837
Let's see you go.

1:01:06.837 --> 1:01:08.142
It wouldn't be because

1:01:08.142 --> 1:01:12.146
we were excommunicated
or exiled.

1:01:12.146 --> 1:01:15.062
It would be
a supreme act of faith...

1:01:15.062 --> 1:01:16.716
Come on, let's go. Let's go.

1:01:16.716 --> 1:01:20.764
...a step towards
love and forgiveness.

1:01:25.029 --> 1:01:28.554
Leaving is how
we demonstrate our faith.

1:01:30.295 --> 1:01:31.644
We are leaving because

1:01:31.644 --> 1:01:34.821
our faith is stronger
than the rules.

1:01:38.738 --> 1:01:40.392
Bigger than our life.

1:02:04.372 --> 1:02:06.679
I'm sorry.
But I think I might be dying.

1:02:12.816 --> 1:02:15.688
Mother, you're not dying.

1:02:15.688 --> 1:02:17.734
Your glasses need cleaning.

1:02:23.391 --> 1:02:25.524
Why are you laughing?

1:02:26.960 --> 1:02:28.919
We cannot leave.

1:02:29.528 --> 1:02:31.486
We...

1:02:31.486 --> 1:02:34.272
It would be better
to stay and fight than leave.

1:02:34.272 --> 1:02:35.708
Do you really mean
that you want to stay

1:02:35.708 --> 1:02:38.015
and not fight?

1:02:38.015 --> 1:02:39.973
Because when was the last time
you had the strength

1:02:39.973 --> 1:02:41.845
to stand up
to the aggression of Klaas,

1:02:41.845 --> 1:02:43.455
to protect your children,

1:02:43.455 --> 1:02:45.544
- or to get out of harm's way?
-  Who are you

1:02:45.544 --> 1:02:47.502
to tell me what kind of
wife and mother to be

1:02:47.502 --> 1:02:48.939
when you are
neither one yourself?

1:02:48.939 --> 1:02:51.724
You are a spinster. A whore!

1:02:51.724 --> 1:02:53.160
- An unwed mother!
- Stop.

1:02:53.160 --> 1:02:54.248
Ona was
made unconscious

1:02:54.248 --> 1:02:55.423
and raped like the rest of us.

1:02:55.423 --> 1:02:57.861
How dare you call her a whore!

1:02:57.861 --> 1:02:59.906
Mariche, are you not afraid
that your own sweet boys

1:02:59.906 --> 1:03:01.299
will become monsters
like their father

1:03:01.299 --> 1:03:02.822
because you do nothing
to protect them?

1:03:02.822 --> 1:03:04.258
- Stop it!
- Nothing to educate them,

1:03:04.258 --> 1:03:05.520
nothing to teach them

1:03:05.520 --> 1:03:06.826
the horror of
their father's ways...

1:03:06.826 --> 1:03:10.177
I have heard enough!

1:03:10.177 --> 1:03:13.615
Do you women realize
we are talking about leaving?

1:03:13.615 --> 1:03:17.054
We are a large group.
Many things could go wrong.

1:03:17.054 --> 1:03:18.272
And time is fleeting.

1:03:18.272 --> 1:03:20.231
For the love
of our Lord Jesus Christ

1:03:20.231 --> 1:03:21.710
and precious Savior,

1:03:21.710 --> 1:03:24.235
shut your pie holes, please!

1:03:29.414 --> 1:03:32.156
How dare you
pass judgment on me?

1:03:32.156 --> 1:03:34.027
It wasn't a judgment.
It was a question.

1:03:44.516 --> 1:03:46.387
Tell her you're sorry.

1:03:50.304 --> 1:03:52.306
I'm sorry.

1:03:52.306 --> 1:03:53.655
I'm sorry that
what I said hurt you.

1:03:53.655 --> 1:03:54.961
Oh, fuck it off!

1:03:54.961 --> 1:03:56.223
Sit down, Mariche!

1:03:56.223 --> 1:03:57.616
It's "fuck off" I think.

1:03:57.616 --> 1:03:58.660
Shh!

1:04:00.227 --> 1:04:02.534
I am sorry.

1:04:02.534 --> 1:04:04.753
I'm saying sorry, not just
to leave the hurt behind,

1:04:04.753 --> 1:04:06.320
but because I feel truly

1:04:06.320 --> 1:04:08.670
that I should not have
said something harmful to you.

1:04:10.237 --> 1:04:11.717
And Mariche, I'm sorry

1:04:11.717 --> 1:04:15.068
because you do not
need or deserve any more harm.

1:04:17.418 --> 1:04:18.985
Who are you?

1:04:20.247 --> 1:04:22.075
Who are any of you

1:04:23.033 --> 1:04:25.992
to pretend
I have had a choice?

1:04:43.140 --> 1:04:47.057
I am also sorry, Mariche.

1:04:47.057 --> 1:04:51.931
I didn't try to protect you
or your children from Klaas.

1:04:51.931 --> 1:04:55.587
And what you say is true.
You had no choice.

1:04:55.587 --> 1:04:59.504
You forgave him,
again and again,

1:05:00.244 --> 1:05:01.898
as you were told to.

1:05:05.423 --> 1:05:07.120
As I told you to.

1:05:09.253 --> 1:05:10.515
I'm sorry.

1:05:12.299 --> 1:05:13.866
I'm sorry.

1:05:16.913 --> 1:05:18.436
I'm sorry.

1:05:38.847 --> 1:05:40.284
It's not only the men and boys

1:05:40.284 --> 1:05:42.503
who have been
excellent students.

1:05:54.689 --> 1:05:58.519
I think Mariche,
we are all very sorry.

1:05:58.519 --> 1:06:01.174
What you were required
to endure was a...

1:06:01.174 --> 1:06:04.003
Misuse of forgiveness.

1:06:04.003 --> 1:06:05.744
Is there such a thing?

1:06:05.744 --> 1:06:08.051
A forgiveness
that is not good?

1:06:08.051 --> 1:06:10.879
Perhaps forgiveness
can in some instances

1:06:10.879 --> 1:06:13.795
be confused with permission.

1:06:50.441 --> 1:06:51.920
What in heaven's name?

1:06:53.879 --> 1:06:55.620
What is it?
Julius, what is it?

1:06:59.189 --> 1:07:01.017
Nettie, please.
Make an exception

1:07:01.017 --> 1:07:02.453
and tell us what is happening.

1:07:03.541 --> 1:07:05.064
What has happened to him?

1:07:06.631 --> 1:07:08.198
Nettie, be realistic.

1:07:08.198 --> 1:07:10.026
Tell us what has happened
to Julius.

1:07:10.026 --> 1:07:11.505
Speak. Just this once.

1:07:12.376 --> 1:07:13.986
What's wrong, sweetheart?

1:07:13.986 --> 1:07:16.945
My nose.
There's a cherry up my nose.

1:07:16.945 --> 1:07:18.730
Okay, well, blow.

1:07:18.730 --> 1:07:21.211
- Harder. Again.

1:07:24.823 --> 1:07:26.042
There you go.

1:07:26.042 --> 1:07:27.913
We have no cherries
in the colony.

1:07:30.089 --> 1:07:32.309
Klaas sometimes brings them
back from the city.

1:07:32.309 --> 1:07:34.572
Who gave you
the cherries, Julius?

1:07:34.572 --> 1:07:36.052
Papa.

1:07:38.706 --> 1:07:39.925
Why don't you...

1:07:39.925 --> 1:07:41.361
You go and play
with Nettie, all right?

1:07:48.803 --> 1:07:50.283
Have we
made a decision?

1:07:50.283 --> 1:07:51.719
Are we leaving?

1:07:53.721 --> 1:07:54.722
Yes.

1:07:55.810 --> 1:07:56.855
We are leaving because...

1:07:56.855 --> 1:07:58.117
We know why we are leaving.

1:07:58.117 --> 1:08:00.076
We are leaving
because we cannot stay.

1:08:03.992 --> 1:08:05.168
Hmm.

1:08:05.168 --> 1:08:06.691
We will take young boys of 12
with us.

1:08:06.691 --> 1:08:08.432
Allow the men
to join the women later

1:08:08.432 --> 1:08:10.216
under certain conditions.

1:08:10.869 --> 1:08:12.392
- No.
- No.

1:08:12.392 --> 1:08:14.090
Aaron. I know.

1:08:14.090 --> 1:08:16.222
Aaron is just over 12.
Just barely.

1:08:16.222 --> 1:08:18.529
Why would boys
of 13 and 14 be left behind?

1:08:18.529 --> 1:08:19.704
Why wouldn't
they leave with us?

1:08:19.704 --> 1:08:21.184
Surely, we don't
have to be afraid

1:08:21.184 --> 1:08:22.533
of the boys of this age.

1:08:22.533 --> 1:08:24.012
August, you're
the boys' teacher.

1:08:24.012 --> 1:08:25.927
What is your feeling
about this?

1:08:25.927 --> 1:08:27.146
Do boys of that age

1:08:27.146 --> 1:08:29.061
pose a risk
to our girls and women?

1:08:33.283 --> 1:08:35.328
Yes. Possibly.

1:08:35.328 --> 1:08:37.461
Boys of 13 or 14 are capable

1:08:37.461 --> 1:08:40.290
of causing great damage
to girls and women.

1:08:41.726 --> 1:08:43.510
And to each other.

1:08:45.382 --> 1:08:47.427
It is a brash age.

1:08:47.427 --> 1:08:50.865
They are possessed
of reckless urges,

1:08:50.865 --> 1:08:52.519
physical exuberance,

1:08:52.519 --> 1:08:56.784
intense curiosity
that often results in injury.

1:08:58.699 --> 1:09:00.962
Unbridled emotion,

1:09:00.962 --> 1:09:04.183
including deep tenderness
and empathy,

1:09:04.183 --> 1:09:05.532
and not quite enough

1:09:05.532 --> 1:09:07.795
experience
or brain development

1:09:07.795 --> 1:09:09.971
to fully understand
or appreciate

1:09:09.971 --> 1:09:12.844
the consequences
of their words or actions.

1:09:12.844 --> 1:09:14.367
They are like the yearlings.

1:09:15.760 --> 1:09:19.590
Young, awkward,
gleeful, powerful.

1:09:21.244 --> 1:09:22.767
They're tall, muscular,

1:09:22.767 --> 1:09:24.290
sexually inquisitive creatures,

1:09:24.290 --> 1:09:27.511
with little impulse control,
but they are children.

1:09:33.256 --> 1:09:35.388
They are children
and they can be taught.

1:09:37.825 --> 1:09:40.088
I'm a two-bit schoolteacher,

1:09:40.088 --> 1:09:41.916
a failed farmer,

1:09:41.916 --> 1:09:45.224
and above all a believer.

1:09:45.224 --> 1:09:48.140
And I believe
that with guidance,

1:09:48.140 --> 1:09:51.361
firm love and patience,

1:09:51.361 --> 1:09:53.450
these boys are capable
of relearning

1:09:53.450 --> 1:09:55.582
their roles as males
in the colony.

1:10:02.807 --> 1:10:05.592
I believe in
what the great poet

1:10:05.592 --> 1:10:07.203
Samuel Taylor Coleridge

1:10:07.203 --> 1:10:10.206
thought were the cardinal
rules of early education.

1:10:11.424 --> 1:10:12.947
"To work by love

1:10:14.732 --> 1:10:17.082
"and so generate love.

1:10:18.170 --> 1:10:19.606
"To habituate the mind

1:10:19.606 --> 1:10:21.826
"to intellectual
accuracy and truth.

1:10:22.827 --> 1:10:25.873
"To excite imaginative power."

1:10:29.703 --> 1:10:31.401
He said,

1:10:31.401 --> 1:10:35.927
"Little is taught
by contest or dispute,

1:10:35.927 --> 1:10:39.191
"everything by
sympathy and love."

1:10:48.896 --> 1:10:51.203
I believe the boys
should be allowed

1:10:51.203 --> 1:10:52.683
to leave with the women...

1:10:55.773 --> 1:10:58.428
Providing the women
choose to leave.

1:10:58.428 --> 1:11:00.125
It was a yes
or no question.

1:11:00.125 --> 1:11:03.346
You shit like any other man,
why don't you talk like one?

1:11:07.437 --> 1:11:08.438
Sorry.

1:11:11.179 --> 1:11:13.312
I have a proposal
to make.

1:11:13.312 --> 1:11:16.010
We have to protect
all of our children.

1:11:16.010 --> 1:11:17.751
Not only our daughters.

1:11:17.751 --> 1:11:20.276
Every boy under 15

1:11:20.276 --> 1:11:22.234
and the ones
who need special care

1:11:22.234 --> 1:11:24.497
must accompany the women.

1:11:24.497 --> 1:11:25.933
How do you mean must?

1:11:25.933 --> 1:11:27.195
What if they refuse?

1:11:27.195 --> 1:11:28.414
What if they
don't want to leave?

1:11:28.414 --> 1:11:31.504
We can't carry teenagers
on our backs.

1:11:31.504 --> 1:11:33.941
We will try
to influence our sons.

1:11:33.941 --> 1:11:35.378
But we cannot force them,

1:11:35.378 --> 1:11:37.380
and they might refuse,
it's true.

1:11:37.380 --> 1:11:38.598
August...

1:11:40.687 --> 1:11:44.300
you would stay and teach
the boys who remain?

1:11:45.388 --> 1:11:46.345
Of course.

1:12:02.666 --> 1:12:04.320
He's right outside.

1:12:06.626 --> 1:12:07.932
Klaas?

1:12:12.589 --> 1:12:14.199
He has Ruth and Cheryl.

1:12:16.767 --> 1:12:19.683
Everybody, back to your houses
and pack up.

1:12:19.683 --> 1:12:22.338
If anyone asks,
we were quilting.

1:12:22.338 --> 1:12:25.297
August, uh, get the map.

1:12:25.297 --> 1:12:26.516
Neitje and Autje,

1:12:26.516 --> 1:12:28.431
you must run right now
to every house

1:12:28.431 --> 1:12:29.997
and tell the women,
we are leaving.

1:12:29.997 --> 1:12:31.259
Tell them to pack up
everything they can

1:12:31.259 --> 1:12:32.391
and to meet us
outside the washhouse

1:12:32.391 --> 1:12:34.001
an hour after sunrise.

1:12:34.001 --> 1:12:35.438
We need to get
an early start in the morning.

1:12:35.438 --> 1:12:38.049
Let's all meet back here
at sunrise.

1:12:38.049 --> 1:12:39.093
All of us.

1:12:42.270 --> 1:12:43.620
An hour after sunrise.

1:12:43.620 --> 1:12:45.056
We congregate on the road
by the washhouse.

1:12:45.056 --> 1:12:47.275
- Do we bring...
- Everything. Bring everything.

1:12:47.841 --> 1:12:48.929
Why?

1:12:56.937 --> 1:12:58.722
- After sunrise... All right?
- Wake up.

1:12:58.722 --> 1:13:00.463
Tomorrow one hour
after sunrise.

1:13:00.463 --> 1:13:01.594
We're leaving after sunrise.

1:13:23.094 --> 1:13:25.313
We meet an hour after sunrise
on this road.

1:13:25.313 --> 1:13:26.489
Bring your buggies.

1:13:26.489 --> 1:13:27.925
Thank you, sister.

1:13:40.590 --> 1:13:42.374
Who can get home
the quickest, huh?

1:13:42.374 --> 1:13:44.463
She has a cricket
in her hands.

1:13:44.463 --> 1:13:45.595
You do?

1:13:47.292 --> 1:13:49.163
Can I see? Okay.

1:13:55.474 --> 1:13:56.736
Yes. Bed time.

1:13:57.258 --> 1:13:58.390
Yes.

1:13:58.390 --> 1:14:00.174
Don't go.

1:14:00.174 --> 1:14:04.178
Stay with me tonight.
Or I will go with you.

1:14:04.178 --> 1:14:06.616
If I don't go home, it'll draw
attention to all of us.

1:14:06.616 --> 1:14:09.183
- Mariche.
- Go home, Mother.

1:14:09.183 --> 1:14:11.055
I'll see you at sunrise.

1:14:50.094 --> 1:14:52.052
They said later,
it should have taken longer

1:14:52.052 --> 1:14:53.750
to pack up a whole life.

1:14:54.664 --> 1:14:56.361
It was disappointing

1:14:56.361 --> 1:14:58.668
to realize that everything
that ever mattered to you

1:14:58.668 --> 1:15:00.452
could be gathered up
in a few short hours.

1:15:04.587 --> 1:15:07.198
We would leave
only traces of ourselves.

1:15:22.605 --> 1:15:24.084
Go. Go.

1:15:32.484 --> 1:15:34.355
Psst. August!

1:15:36.662 --> 1:15:38.011
Come sit with me.

1:15:42.799 --> 1:15:43.887
Here's the map.

1:15:47.891 --> 1:15:49.153
Where are we?

1:15:51.808 --> 1:15:52.896
Here.

1:15:54.201 --> 1:15:55.246
Here?

1:15:55.246 --> 1:15:56.290
Mm-hmm.

1:15:57.596 --> 1:15:59.467
This is where we are.

1:16:06.431 --> 1:16:11.610
This is north, south,
east, and west.

1:16:12.263 --> 1:16:13.612
But the map moves.

1:16:13.612 --> 1:16:15.875
How do you know
which way it should be facing?

1:16:17.137 --> 1:16:19.487
Celestial navigation.

1:16:20.140 --> 1:16:21.794
I can show you.

1:16:27.626 --> 1:16:29.236
Do you know
of the Southern Cross?

1:16:29.236 --> 1:16:30.281
Mm-hmm.

1:16:31.151 --> 1:16:32.413
You and the women

1:16:32.413 --> 1:16:35.852
can use the Southern Cross
to navigate.

1:16:37.288 --> 1:16:39.420
If you, um,

1:16:39.420 --> 1:16:42.467
make your right hand
into a fist...

1:16:46.689 --> 1:16:51.563
Align the first knuckle
with the axis of the Cross.

1:16:53.043 --> 1:16:56.263
And then the tip
of your thumb here

1:16:56.263 --> 1:16:58.048
will indicate south.

1:17:08.798 --> 1:17:10.800
Will you show the others?

1:17:12.671 --> 1:17:15.413
We will have
a lesson in navigation.

1:17:17.545 --> 1:17:20.505
Did you already know
about this little trick?

1:17:23.160 --> 1:17:24.640
Of course, I did.

1:17:24.640 --> 1:17:26.598
I wish there was something
I could teach you

1:17:26.598 --> 1:17:29.166
that you didn't already know.

1:17:49.926 --> 1:17:52.711
What will become of you
when we leave?

1:18:17.257 --> 1:18:20.826
You make a fist
with your right hand.

1:18:20.826 --> 1:18:24.743
And point your two knuckles
to the Southern Cross.

1:18:24.743 --> 1:18:27.441
It's called
celestial navigation.

1:18:33.970 --> 1:18:36.059
Point these two knuckles.

1:18:40.803 --> 1:18:41.891
Like that?

1:18:41.891 --> 1:18:42.935
Mm-hmm.

1:18:48.419 --> 1:18:50.900
And wherever your thumb
is pointing that's south.

1:19:08.439 --> 1:19:11.485
We like to put
frames around things.

1:19:11.485 --> 1:19:14.837
Even when they
are spilling out the edges.

1:19:14.837 --> 1:19:17.796
So, we gathered
one last time in the hayloft,

1:19:17.796 --> 1:19:19.450
where so much had been said.

1:19:21.147 --> 1:19:23.019
So much that your grandmother
would have told you,

1:19:23.019 --> 1:19:24.498
had you ever met.

1:19:46.956 --> 1:19:48.087
Is he gone?

1:19:49.872 --> 1:19:51.743
He's sleeping.

1:19:51.743 --> 1:19:53.266
Dead to the world.

1:19:55.399 --> 1:19:57.183
He was very drunk.

1:20:00.230 --> 1:20:01.405
And he caught me

1:20:01.405 --> 1:20:03.711
sneaking back
into the house late,

1:20:05.148 --> 1:20:06.497
and then he went to the barn

1:20:06.497 --> 1:20:09.674
and found we had
taken the horses.

1:20:09.674 --> 1:20:13.809
Mariche, did you
tell him what we are planning?

1:20:13.809 --> 1:20:15.723
She did. But only because
he wouldn't stop hitting me

1:20:15.723 --> 1:20:17.421
and she was trying
to distract him.

1:20:17.421 --> 1:20:19.640
I don't think
he believed me.

1:20:19.640 --> 1:20:21.860
And even if he did,
I don't think he'll remember.

1:20:21.860 --> 1:20:24.080
He'll be passed out
all morning I'm sure.

1:20:27.692 --> 1:20:30.956
But I also told him because
I suddenly felt very...

1:20:46.406 --> 1:20:48.756
We have decided
that we want...

1:20:51.759 --> 1:20:52.935
That we are...

1:20:55.459 --> 1:20:58.592
We are entitled
to three things.

1:21:01.421 --> 1:21:02.596
What are they?

1:21:07.819 --> 1:21:10.300
We want our children
to be safe.

1:21:22.616 --> 1:21:23.835
We want...

1:21:23.835 --> 1:21:27.621
We want to be steadfast
in our faith.

1:21:31.147 --> 1:21:33.279
And we want to think.

1:21:36.804 --> 1:21:37.805
Yes.

1:21:41.635 --> 1:21:43.115
Praise God.

1:22:05.442 --> 1:22:07.313
Yeah. We all want that.

1:22:08.662 --> 1:22:14.320
♪ Nearer, my God, to Thee ♪

1:22:14.320 --> 1:22:18.759
- ♪ Nearer to Thee ♪
- ♪ To Thee ♪

1:22:18.759 --> 1:22:24.374
♪ E'en though it be a cross ♪

1:22:24.374 --> 1:22:27.594
♪ That raiseth me ♪

1:22:29.509 --> 1:22:34.384
♪ Still all my song shall be ♪

1:22:34.384 --> 1:22:45.047
♪ Nearer, my God, to Thee ♪

1:22:46.048 --> 1:22:50.269
♪ Nearer to Thee ♪

1:22:52.315 --> 1:22:56.493
♪ Though like the wanderer ♪

1:22:57.885 --> 1:23:01.933
♪ The sun gone down ♪

1:23:03.848 --> 1:23:09.636
♪ Darkness be over me ♪

1:23:09.636 --> 1:23:13.553
♪ My rest a stone ♪

1:23:15.599 --> 1:23:19.211
♪ Yet in my dreams I'd be ♪

1:23:21.257 --> 1:23:32.920
♪ Nearer, my God, to Thee ♪

1:23:32.920 --> 1:23:38.100
♪ Nearer to Thee ♪

1:23:39.231 --> 1:23:44.106
♪ There let the way appear ♪

1:23:45.281 --> 1:23:49.024
♪ Steps unto heav'n ♪

1:23:50.938 --> 1:23:56.683
♪ All that thou sendest me ♪

1:23:56.683 --> 1:24:02.167
♪ In mercy giv'n ♪

1:24:02.167 --> 1:24:03.473
Let's go.

1:24:05.127 --> 1:24:06.476
I saw your brother.

1:24:06.476 --> 1:24:07.912
Careful! We're gonna get you.

1:24:07.912 --> 1:24:10.045
Help me, I'm tied up.

1:24:12.177 --> 1:24:13.396
Where are they?

1:24:15.528 --> 1:24:16.747
Look there.

1:24:19.924 --> 1:24:23.362
♪ Nearer to Thee ♪

1:24:25.712 --> 1:24:31.849
♪ Nearer, my God, to Thee ♪

1:24:31.849 --> 1:24:37.159
♪ Nearer to Thee ♪

1:24:52.870 --> 1:24:54.350
Just...

1:24:54.350 --> 1:24:55.873
August, you can speak
whenever you want.

1:24:55.873 --> 1:24:58.223
You don't have
to raise your hand.

1:25:01.008 --> 1:25:02.009
I...

1:25:05.839 --> 1:25:07.232
It's all right.

1:25:09.321 --> 1:25:10.801
It wasn't important.

1:25:17.590 --> 1:25:18.939
Oh.

1:25:22.117 --> 1:25:24.119
Are the children
clean and ready?

1:25:28.949 --> 1:25:30.864
Thank you, Melvin.

1:25:33.171 --> 1:25:35.260
Thank you for saying my name.

1:25:37.784 --> 1:25:40.004
We hid Ruth and Cheryl
for you.

1:25:40.004 --> 1:25:41.397
They are ready to go.

1:25:41.397 --> 1:25:42.920
Really?

1:25:43.573 --> 1:25:46.619
Well, oh, my girls.

1:25:48.969 --> 1:25:50.754
Has Aaron readied
the horses for us?

1:25:53.670 --> 1:25:54.975
What? Well, where is he?

1:25:56.977 --> 1:25:58.065
Where is he?

1:25:58.762 --> 1:26:00.285
- No.
- Speak to me.

1:26:00.285 --> 1:26:01.852
-  You're safe, Melvin.
- Please, speak to me.

1:26:01.852 --> 1:26:02.853
No, no, no. I won't harm you.
I'm not your enemy!

1:26:02.853 --> 1:26:03.897
You have to be calm, Salome.

1:26:03.897 --> 1:26:05.812
- No!
- Aaron will be found.

1:26:05.812 --> 1:26:07.510
I'm not leaving without him.

1:26:11.601 --> 1:26:13.907
Salome, come back!

1:26:17.824 --> 1:26:19.739
What if she
doesn't convince him?

1:26:23.439 --> 1:26:24.440
Mother?

1:26:27.530 --> 1:26:28.574
Breathe.

1:26:29.401 --> 1:26:30.489
Breathe.

1:26:36.756 --> 1:26:38.280
We are going to go now.

1:26:43.154 --> 1:26:45.287
I'm all right. Please go.

1:26:45.287 --> 1:26:47.767
Come on, let's go.

1:26:49.029 --> 1:26:50.030
Now?

1:26:50.553 --> 1:26:51.554
Yes.

1:26:52.424 --> 1:26:53.773
Make a list, August.

1:26:55.297 --> 1:26:56.776
A list of what?

1:26:56.776 --> 1:26:58.256
Of good things.

1:26:58.256 --> 1:27:00.519
Of plans, of memories.

1:27:00.519 --> 1:27:02.695
Whatever you feel
goes into a good list.

1:27:03.653 --> 1:27:05.742
What we, the women
will want there.

1:27:05.742 --> 1:27:06.786
Please write it down.

1:27:09.093 --> 1:27:10.268
August.

1:27:11.965 --> 1:27:14.620
Thank you for all you've done.

1:27:14.620 --> 1:27:17.275
We are all so proud of you.

1:27:22.976 --> 1:27:25.501
And your mother
would be proud too.

1:27:32.769 --> 1:27:34.292
I'll make a list.

1:27:37.208 --> 1:27:39.341
This is going
to be a difficult trip.

1:27:39.341 --> 1:27:42.213
Today is the day
the Lord hath made.

1:27:43.736 --> 1:27:44.998
Rejoice...

1:27:47.349 --> 1:27:48.741
and be glad in it.

1:27:53.268 --> 1:27:54.965
Go join the others.

1:27:55.879 --> 1:27:57.054
Please.

1:28:06.585 --> 1:28:09.458
I will not be buried
in this colony.

1:28:11.460 --> 1:28:15.202
Get me into a buggy now
and let me die on the trail.

1:28:16.508 --> 1:28:18.423
But what about August?

1:28:18.423 --> 1:28:19.511
Oh!

1:28:24.124 --> 1:28:25.430
He'll be fine.

1:28:32.045 --> 1:28:33.656
He'll be fine.

1:28:55.417 --> 1:28:56.722
Hang on with both hands.

1:29:08.778 --> 1:29:09.779
Ona!

1:29:15.915 --> 1:29:17.395
I will always love you.

1:29:40.157 --> 1:29:42.594
She loves you too, August.

1:29:42.594 --> 1:29:44.509
She loves everyone.

1:30:23.679 --> 1:30:25.289
Sun.

1:30:29.598 --> 1:30:31.251
Stars.

1:30:33.863 --> 1:30:35.473
Pails.

1:30:38.476 --> 1:30:40.130
The harvest.

1:30:43.742 --> 1:30:45.265
Numbers.

1:30:47.398 --> 1:30:48.660
Window.

1:30:51.141 --> 1:30:52.490
Straw.

1:30:55.014 --> 1:30:56.407
Sounds.

1:30:59.628 --> 1:31:01.194
Beams.

1:31:07.026 --> 1:31:08.463
Love.

1:31:11.683 --> 1:31:13.946
All right. We'll go.

1:31:21.388 --> 1:31:22.694
Language.

1:31:26.481 --> 1:31:27.873
Wind.

1:31:32.617 --> 1:31:34.010
Women.

1:31:43.672 --> 1:31:44.847
Salome?

1:31:49.068 --> 1:31:50.766
We may need
to protect ourselves.

1:31:52.724 --> 1:31:53.769
Where is Aaron?

1:31:55.205 --> 1:31:56.989
He's in the buggy, waiting.

1:31:58.077 --> 1:31:59.731
You convinced him to leave?

1:32:01.254 --> 1:32:02.473
You may need this.

1:32:03.909 --> 1:32:05.215
For protection.

1:32:06.912 --> 1:32:08.000
Did you?

1:32:10.437 --> 1:32:11.917
- Did you have...?
- Yes!

1:32:11.917 --> 1:32:14.093
He's coming with me.
He's my child.

1:32:26.497 --> 1:32:27.672
Goodbye, August.

1:32:29.674 --> 1:32:30.806
Good luck.

1:32:32.242 --> 1:32:35.114
Please take care
of Ona and her baby.

1:32:35.114 --> 1:32:37.029
Of course. I promise.

1:32:37.029 --> 1:32:38.857
Wait. I need
to give you something.

1:32:38.857 --> 1:32:40.380
No! I have to go!

1:32:46.909 --> 1:32:47.910
Here.

1:32:51.783 --> 1:32:53.350
Why have you
got a gun, August?

1:33:08.321 --> 1:33:10.193
Don't kill yourself, August.

1:33:11.542 --> 1:33:13.500
You have important work to do.

1:33:16.808 --> 1:33:19.985
You are the boys' teacher.

1:33:31.388 --> 1:33:32.607
Don't come back.

1:33:34.130 --> 1:33:36.132
Don't ever come back.
Any of you.

1:33:41.746 --> 1:33:43.095
Oh, wait. I need...

1:33:43.095 --> 1:33:44.357
No.

1:33:47.360 --> 1:33:48.492
Please.

1:33:48.492 --> 1:33:50.842
Please, Salome,
give these to Ona.

1:33:50.842 --> 1:33:52.452
But, no...
But she can't read them.

1:33:53.323 --> 1:33:55.020
Her child will read them.

1:33:56.587 --> 1:33:58.720
No, August.

1:33:58.720 --> 1:34:02.375
The purpose was for you
to take the minutes.

1:34:16.389 --> 1:34:17.739
We'll meet again.

1:34:18.740 --> 1:34:20.045
We'll meet again.

1:34:57.779 --> 1:34:59.476
Girls, now,
those can go in the back.

1:34:59.476 --> 1:35:00.607
That's fine.

1:35:02.261 --> 1:35:04.742
We have
more room back here.

1:35:04.742 --> 1:35:05.787
No, but thank you.

1:35:06.962 --> 1:35:08.659
Do you have
any more room?

1:35:08.659 --> 1:35:10.269
We have room
for one more.

1:35:11.967 --> 1:35:14.099
Or two little ones.

1:35:14.099 --> 1:35:15.710
She can sit
on my lap.

1:35:17.886 --> 1:35:19.365
It's sturdy now.

1:35:19.365 --> 1:35:21.193
Come with me.
Follow me.

1:35:23.587 --> 1:35:25.763
It's all right,
sisters. It's all right.

1:35:33.205 --> 1:35:35.381
Up, up.
There you go.

1:35:36.426 --> 1:35:38.036
Hold the baby
for now.

1:35:38.036 --> 1:35:39.690
You'll be riding
with your brother.

1:35:39.690 --> 1:35:40.691
I need a little
more rope to tie this down.

1:35:40.691 --> 1:35:41.692
I have some here.

1:35:49.004 --> 1:35:50.135
Are we all in?

1:36:03.322 --> 1:36:04.323
All right.

1:36:17.772 --> 1:36:19.512
So happy. Come on.

1:36:20.470 --> 1:36:21.688
Come on. Here.

1:37:37.895 --> 1:37:39.114
Shh, shh, shh.

1:37:45.033 --> 1:37:48.253
Your story will be
different from ours.
